            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002706_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I sent to the <placeName><geogName type="region">Cape</geogName></placeName> for <measure>£150</measure> to
<lb/><seg rend="small">be left in <persName><choice><abbr>Col.<hi rend="sup">e</hi></abbr><expan>Colonel</expan></choice> Nunes</persName>' hands.</seg>
<lb/>Pay <persName>Fito</persName> for <measure>46 or 50 panjas</measure> <!-- I'm unsure what paujas are, but I assume they are some form of measurement? Can't find anything looking it up. BL-->
<lb/>of clean <term type="foodstuff">rice</term> and anything
<lb/>else he may send - <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>also
<lb/><measure>£18</measure> to <persName><choice><abbr>S<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>Seniore</expan></choice> Manuel</persName>'s agent
<lb/>for the <term type="animal">sheep</term> and <term type="animal">goats</term>
<lb/>we <choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> - or rather
<lb/>place the money in <persName><choice><abbr>S<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>Seniore</expan></choice>
<lb/>Galdino</persName>'s hands to be
<lb/>given on receipt of <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi>
<lb/><choice><sic>Thorntons</sic><corr>Thornton's</corr></choice></persName> bill of exchange.
<lb/>Pay <persName>Ali</persName> &amp; <persName>Mabruck</persName>
<lb/>at the rate of six dollars
<lb/><add place="marginleft" rend="small"><w><gap extent="1" unit="chars"/><supplied>p</supplied>er</w> month</add>per month for <persName>Ali</persName> that is
<lb/>5 of agreement &amp; one
<lb/>of backshish - and four
<lb/>dollars per month as per
<lb/>agreement 13 &amp; 1 of backshish
<lb/>and send the amount

	<pb facs="liv_002706_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>given in a note to <del type="strikethrough"><term type="occupation">Captain</term></del>
<lb/><persName><term type="occupation">Admiral</term> Washington</persName> - the <w>dat<gap extent="2" unit="chars"/><supplied>es</supplied></w><!-- quite obvious Livingstone meant to have "dates", as he talks about dates right after, but only "dat" shows up on page. BL. -->
<lb/>are from <date when="1862-03-21">21<hi rend="sup underline">st</hi> March 1863</date>
<lb/>to the probable arrival at
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName>.</p>
<lb/><p>Make urgent representations
<lb/>to the <term type="occupation">Captain</term> of any man of 
<lb/>war as to the necesity of
<lb/>sending into <placeName><geogName type="settlement"><choice><orig>Quillimane</orig><reg>Quelimane</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above"> or <placeName><geogName type="settlement">Kongone</geogName></placeName></add><!-- I believe I normalized these correctly, but I'm not completely sure that's how Livingstone write them. Please review. BL--> in
<lb/>supply of provisions and <w>ma<gap extent="2" unit="chars"/><supplied>ke</supplied></w>
<lb/>any arrangements you can
<lb/>to have them sent up quickly -
<lb/>If necessary write an official
<lb/>letter and on his refusal
<lb/>send a copy to the <name>Foreign off<supplied>ice</supplied></name></p>
<lb/><p>If there is any difficulty
<lb/>with <persName>Tito</persName> - Try if <persName><choice><abbr>Col.<hi rend="sup">e</hi></abbr><expan>Colonel</expan></choice> Nunes</persName>
<lb/>will undertake to said <term type="foodstuff">rice</term> &amp;
<lb/>and provisions &amp; pay himsel<supplied>f</supplied>
<lb/>out of the money which is to
<lb/>be delivered to him namely <measure>£150</measure></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>



            </div>
